cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method to enhance the discriminability of CNNs for large-scale image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm to learn the tree structure, which involves training the network on a subset of classes. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with image classification, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to boost the performance of a given basic CNN model, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
